ds them now\n```\n\n**3. Execution-Trace Review**\n\nThis caught the double-canonicalize issue in `but-agentlog`, so I’d encode it:\n\n```md\n## Execution-Trace Review\n\nFor non-trivial changes, do one review pass by following the runtime path from\nthe public entry point downward. Look for repeated validation, repeated parsing,\nstate rediscovery, unnecessary conversions, and names that no longer match what\nthe code actually does.\n```\n\n**4. De-Aggress Clippy Fix**\n\nI’d still change the current `clippy --fix --allow-dirty` default. Not because of dirty worktrees, but because automatic fixing can create mechanical churn.\n\n```md\nRun `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy` before finishing. Use `cargo clippy --fix`\nonly when the suggested edits are clearly in scope and you inspect the diff.\n```\n\nThat combo feels more directly aimed at what you care about: fewer ceremonial APIs, less fake extensibility, names that match semantics, and fewer “looks structured but nobody would have written it that way by hand” artifacts.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T20:46:37.760Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}